
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes

class Person {
  +personID: int
  +phone: String
  +keywords: List<String>
  +institutionCode: int
}

class Institution {
  +institutionCode: int
  +name: String
  +address: String
}

class ScientificArticle {
  +doi: String
  +title: String
}

class Authorship {
  +position: int
}

class PeerReviewedPaper {
  +citationCount: int
}

class TechnicalReport {
  #institutionCode: int
}

class Publisher {
  +name: String
}

class Journal {
  +name: String
  +impactFactor: double
}

class Subscription {
  #institutionCode: int
  #journalName: String
  #publisherName: String
}

class Reviewer {
  +personID: int
}

' Relationships between classes

Person "1" -- "0..*" Authorship : has authorship role in
Authorship "1" -- "1" ScientificArticle : of article
ScientificArticle "1" -- "1" (PeerReviewedPaper, TechnicalReport) : is either a
ScientificArticle "1" -- "1" Person : authored by
ScientificArticle "1" -- "1..*" Reviewer : reviewed by

Institution "1" -- "0..*" Person : employs
Institution "1" -- "0..*" TechnicalReport : publishes
Institution "1" -- "0..*" Subscription : subscribes to

Publisher "1" -- "0..*" Journal : publishes
Journal "1" -- "0..*" Subscription : subscribed by
Journal "1" -- "0..*" PeerReviewedPaper : publishes

TechnicalReport "1" -- "1" Institution : published by
PeerReviewedPaper "1" -- "1" Journal : published in
PeerReviewedPaper "1" -- "1..*" Reviewer : reviewed by

' Generalization relationships
ScientificArticle <|-- PeerReviewedPaper
ScientificArticle <|-- TechnicalReport

@enduml

---

### Notes:
- The `Authorship` class captures the position of an author in a multi-author paper.
- The `Reviewer` class is used to represent a person who reviews a peer-reviewed paper.
- A `Subscription` links an `Institution`, a `Journal`, and a `Publisher`.
- `TechnicalReport` can only be published by one institution, while `PeerReviewedPaper` must be published in a journal.

